---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="50% Tax Break (Article 5C) Greece | Taxomade">
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="mb-16 border-b border-slate-100 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tight">Pay tax on only half your income <span class="text-blue-800">—</span> for 7 years.</h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 mb-8 max-w-3xl">Greece's special regime for newcomers exempts 50% of your Greek income from tax. We handle the application.</p>
      <a href="/#configurator" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold rounded-lg text-white bg-slate-900 hover:bg-blue-800 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-sm">
        See if it's worth it for you
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- What it is -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">What it is</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Under Greece's inbound-worker regime (Article 5C), people who move their tax residency to Greece can have <strong class="text-slate-900">50% of their Greek income exempted from income tax for up to 7 years</strong>. With standard Greek tax rates running from 9% to 44%, this can save you several thousand euros per year. It applies to both employees and freelancers/self-employed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Requirements -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>You must transfer your tax residency to Greece (become a Greek tax resident — i.e. stay 183+ days).</li>
        <li>You must <strong class="text-slate-900">not</strong> have been a Greek tax resident for at least <strong class="text-slate-900">5 of the previous 6 years</strong>.</li>
        <li>You must move from an EU/EEA country or a country with a tax-cooperation agreement with Greece (covers most countries: US, UK, EU, etc.).</li>
        <li>You must commit to staying in Greece for at least two years.</li>
        <li>The benefit scales with income — it's most valuable at higher incomes.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <section class="mb-16 bg-slate-50 p-8 md:p-10 rounded-2xl border border-slate-100">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">How it works</h2>
      
      <div class="mb-6 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-800 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <p class="text-blue-900 font-medium"><em>Timing matters:</em> The application must be filed by <strong class="text-blue-900">31 July</strong> of the relevant year. It's a one-time application that then applies for 7 years.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8 mt-10">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center"><span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-slate-900 text-white flex items-center justify-center mr-3 text-sm">1</span> What you do</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 ml-11">Confirm your situation with us and provide the needed details; we tell you if and when it's worth applying.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center"><span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-800 text-white flex items-center justify-center mr-3 text-sm">2</span> What Taxomade does</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 ml-11">We assess your eligibility, calculate your expected savings, prepare and file the application with the Greek tax authority (AADE), and make sure it's done within the deadline.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Does it work for freelancers?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Yes — employees and self-employed both qualify.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How much can I save?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">It depends on income. At €40,000 income, roughly €5,000/year; the saving grows with income.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How long does it last?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Up to 7 years.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">What's the catch?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">You must genuinely move your tax residency to Greece and not have been a recent Greek tax resident. We check this before applying.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Does it affect my home-country taxes?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Cross-border tax can be complex — we'll flag where you should coordinate with a home-country advisor.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer Disclaimer -->
    <div class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 text-sm text-slate-500">
      <p>Taxomade is not a government body. We coordinate licensed local accountants and lawyers. Information is general and not individual legal or tax advice.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
